        public static double funcs​(java.lang.String parser,
                           java.util.Scanner str,
                           java.util.Scanner n)

        Description:

        This method receive the parser and checks if is a number or not, has the switch with all the functions' cases.

        Pos:

        This method checks if the string in the parser is a number and gives you back the number, if is not a number, then it checks if its a function and what function is and gives you back the result of the function.

        Parameters:
        parser - Is the scanner that receives the number or function and then parse it into a number or checks what function is.
        str - Is a scanner for strings.
        n - Is a scanner for numbers and its used in each method of the functions.
        Returns:
        num Gives back the parsed number or tha result of the functions.
